@node Creating notes
@section Creating notes

@findex org-roam-extras-new-note
@findex org-roam-extras-convert-heading-to-note
The command @code{org-roam-extras-new-note} creates a new Org Roam note
through a guided workflow.  It first prompts the user to select a note
type: ``generic'', ``person'', ``Borges'', ``tango'', or ``tlon-notes''.  The
type determines the target directory (e.g., @code{paths-dir-notes} for
generic, @code{paths-dir-people} for person) and the initial tags.

After selecting the type, it prompts for the note name, creates a file
with a slugified version of that name (via @code{simple-extras-slugify}),
inserts the @samp{#+title:} line and an initial heading, sets the tags,
creates an Org ID, narrows to the new entry, and places point at the end
of the buffer.

The command @code{org-roam-extras-convert-heading-to-note} extracts the
current Org heading and its subtree from the source buffer, prompts for
a note name (defaulting to the heading title), and creates a new file in
the current directory.  The heading content is moved into the new file,
which gets a @samp{#+title:} line and an adjusted top-level heading.  The
original heading is removed from the source buffer.

@node Finding nodes
@section Finding nodes

@findex org-roam-extras-node-find
@findex org-roam-extras-node-find-special
@findex org-roam-extras-node-select-tag
The command @code{org-roam-extras-node-find} acts as an enhanced wrapper
around @code{org-roam-node-find}.  Before invoking the finder, it widens the
buffer and shows all headings (via @code{org-extras-fold-show-all-headings}).
After jumping to the selected node, it recenters the buffer.

The command @code{org-roam-extras-node-find-special} provides a filtered view
of Org Roam nodes.  It queries the database for nodes that have a
priority, have either no TODO state or the state ``TODO'', and do not have
a SCHEDULED or DEADLINE timestamp.  The results are presented sorted by
priority (ascending, so @samp{#A} appears first).

The command accepts an optional FILTER-SPEC argument:

@itemize
@item
@code{nil}: no additional filter.
@item
@code{t} or a prefix argument: prompt the user to filter by tag or
directory.
@item
@code{(:tag TAG)}: filter by a specific tag.
@item
@code{(:dir DIRECTORY)}: filter by a specific directory.
@end itemize

Selection uses @code{consult--read} for a completing-read interface with
previews.  Jumping to the selected node uses @code{org-id-goto}.

The command @code{org-roam-extras-node-select-tag} prompts for a tag from all
tags present in the Org Roam database.  It is used internally by
@code{org-roam-extras-node-find-special} when filtering by tag.

@node Navigating to nodes
@section Navigating to nodes

@findex org-roam-extras-id-goto
The command @code{org-roam-extras-id-goto} jumps to the location of an Org
ID@.  It widens the buffer both before and after the jump, which handles
the case where the target is in a currently narrowed buffer.  The jump
is performed twice (via @code{org-roam-id-open}) to ensure the correct
position is reached even when narrowing interferes.

@node Replacing star links with ID links
@section Replacing star links with ID links

@findex org-roam-extras-replace-star-links-with-id
The command @code{org-roam-extras-replace-star-links-with-id} walks through
every @samp{.org} file in a given directory and converts links of the form
@code{[[*Title][Description]]} into @code{[[id:UUID][Description]]}, where UUID is
the Org ID of the node whose title matches.

The command is fully automatic: it visits each file, performs the
substitutions (using @code{org-element-map} for robust parsing), and saves
any modified buffers.  When called with a prefix argument (NOCASE), the
title matching is case-insensitive.  An optional DIRS argument restricts
the ID lookup to nodes within specific directories.

Internally, the command uses
@code{org-roam-extras--replace-star-links-with-id-in-file} to process each
file and @code{org-roam-extras-get-id-of-title} to resolve titles to IDs
(@ref{Link utilities}).

