@node Node inclusion
@section Node inclusion

@findex org-roam-extras-node-include-function
The function @code{org-roam-extras-node-include-function} is intended for
@code{org-roam-node-include}.  It returns @code{t} for headings that should
receive an Org ID and be included in the Org Roam database, and @code{nil}
for those that should be excluded.

Exclusion criteria include:

@itemize
@item
Headings tagged with ``noid'' or ``ARCHIVE''.
@item
Headings with specific conventional names such as ``Local variables'',
``Evaluation'', ``History'', ``Further reading'', ``External links'', and
``Related entries''.
@item
Sub-headings (level > 1) in specific directories such as the journal,
Trash, and gptel directories.
@end itemize

@node Backlink tracking
@section Backlink tracking

@findex org-roam-extras-backlink-count
@findex org-roam-extras-update-backlink-count
@findex org-roam-extras-update-modeline
The function @code{org-roam-extras-backlink-count} queries the Org Roam
database for the number of backlinks pointing to the node at point.  It
returns @code{nil} if the buffer is not in @code{org-mode} or if no node ID is
found.

The function @code{org-roam-extras-update-backlink-count} calls
@code{org-roam-extras-backlink-count} and stores the result in the
buffer-local variable @code{org-roam-extras-current-backlink-count}.

The function @code{org-roam-extras-update-modeline} updates the backlink
count and forces a modeline refresh by calling
@code{doom-modeline-update-buffer-file-name}.  It is intended for hooks like
@code{buffer-list-update-hook} to keep the modeline backlink count current.

@node Backlink display
@section Backlink display

@findex org-roam-extras-show-backlink-buffer
The function @code{org-roam-extras-show-backlink-buffer} displays the Org
Roam buffer when visiting a file with backlinks, provided
@code{org-roam-extras-auto-show-backlink-buffer} is non-@code{nil} (@ref{Backlink buffer display}).  It checks whether the Org Roam buffer is already
visible and only displays it if it is not.

@node People directory
@section People directory

@findex org-roam-extras-get-people
The function @code{org-roam-extras-get-people} queries the Org Roam database
for level-1 headings in files within the people directory
(@code{paths-dir-people}).  It returns a list of @samp{(title id)} pairs, useful
for building completion interfaces or reports about contacts.

@node Note creation helpers
@section Note creation helpers

@findex org-roam-extras-get-note-properties
@findex org-roam-extras-create-file-for-note
The function @code{org-roam-extras-get-note-properties} prompts the user to
select a note type and returns a list of @samp{(DIR TAGS)} appropriate for
that type.  It is used by @code{org-roam-extras-new-note}
(@ref{Creating notes}).

The function @code{org-roam-extras-create-file-for-note} creates a file with
a slugified name in the specified directory (defaulting to
@code{paths-dir-notes}).  It signals an error if the file already exists.

@node Link utilities
@section Link utilities

@findex org-roam-extras-get-id-of-title
The function @code{org-roam-extras-get-id-of-title} returns the Org ID of the
node whose title matches exactly.  When NOCASE is non-@code{nil}, the
comparison is case-insensitive.  When DIRS is provided (as a list of
directory paths or a single path), only nodes within those directories
are considered.  An error is signaled if no node or multiple nodes match
the title.

@node Capture support
@section Capture support

@findex org-roam-extras-remove-file-level-properties
The function @code{org-roam-extras-remove-file-level-properties} is intended
for @code{org-capture-before-finalize-hook}.  When the capture template key
is @samp{"r"}, it removes the file-level ``ID'' property and ensures the first
heading receives an Org ID instead.

@node Recent files
@section Recent files

@findex org-roam-extras-recent
The function @code{org-roam-extras-recent} returns a list of Org Roam files
modified within the last DAYS@.  An optional LIMIT argument causes the
function to return the list only if its length is below the limit,
returning @code{nil} otherwise.  The function excludes files matching
@code{org-roam-file-exclude-regexp}.

