@chapter Patched functions

@menu
* Database query delay::
@end menu

@node Database query delay
@section Database query delay

@findex org-roam-db-query
The function @code{org-roam-db-query} is patched using @samp{el-patch} to insert
a 10-millisecond delay (@code{sleep-for 0.01}) before executing each database
query.  This is a workaround for potential SQLite database locking issues
that can arise when rapid successive queries are made, particularly
during bulk operations like indexing or link replacement.

